# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
#
# What NOT to send to the Docker daemon when building Caelo images.
# Docker COPY honours this; smaller build context = faster builds +
# fewer cache invalidations.

# Build artefacts — rebuilt inside the container
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
dist/
**/dist/
build/
**/build/
.svelte-kit/
**/.svelte-kit/
.astro/
**/.astro/
.next/
**/.next/
.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local-only state
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.git/
.github/  # workflows + templates ship to the registry, not into images
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log

# Test + dev outputs
coverage/
**/coverage/
.vitest-cache/
test-results/
**/test-results/
playwright-report/
**/playwright-report/
.playwright/
**/.playwright/

# Static-generator outputs (rebuilt per deploy)
output/
**/output/

# Local Pulumi state + secrets (per-install, never in the image)
.caelo/
.pulumi/
**/Pulumi.*.yaml.bak

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*.bak
*.tmp

# Docs site source — not part of the runtime image
docs-site/
plans/

# CLAUDE.md + CMS_REQUIREMENTS.md + ARCHITECTURE.md — repo-only docs
CLAUDE.md
CMS_REQUIREMENTS.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
CHANGELOG.md
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
SECURITY.md
README.md
LICENSE

# IDE-specific
.zed/
.cursor/
